                <h2>Albert Einstein</h2>
                <h3>Birth-Death</h3>
                <p class="date">March 14, 1879 - April 18, 1955</p>
                
                <p><strong>Fact 1:</strong> Einstein is best known for his theory of relativity, including the famous equation E=mc².</p>
                <p><strong>Fact 2:</strong> He received the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921 for his explanation of the photoelectric effect.</p>
                <p><strong>Fact 3:</strong> Einstein made significant contributions to quantum theory and the understanding of Brownian motion.</p>
                <p><strong>Fact 4:</strong> He published the theory of general relativity in 1915, revolutionizing our understanding of gravity.</p>
                <p><strong>Fact 5:</strong> Einstein was a pacifist and advocated for nuclear disarmament.</p>
