                <h3>Birth-Death</h3>
                <p class="date">November 7, 1867 - July 4, 1934</p>
                
                <p><strong>Fact 1:</strong> Curie was the first woman to win a Nobel Prize and the only person to win Nobel Prizes in two different scientific fields: Physics and Chemistry.</p>
                <p><strong>Fact 2:</strong> She discovered the radioactive elements polonium and radium, pioneering research in radioactivity.</p>
                <p><strong>Fact 3:</strong> Curie's work laid the foundation for the development of nuclear physics and cancer treatment.</p>
                <p><strong>Fact 4:</strong> During World War I, she established mobile radiography units to provide X-rays for diagnosing injured soldiers.</p>
