                <p><strong>Fact 3:</strong> Turing is considered the father of theoretical computer science and artificial intelligence, introducing the concept of the Turing machine.</p>
                <p><strong>Fact 4:</strong> His work on computability and the concept of an algorithm laid the foundation for the field of computer science.</p>
